# 📄 PRD: WhatsApp Insurance Policy Self-Service Feature

---

## 1. 📌 Product Overview

Enable customers to check insurance policy details via WhatsApp chatbot without calling customer support.

### Problem
- High call center load  
- Slow response time  
- Poor customer experience  

### Solution
- Provide instant self-service via WhatsApp chatbot  

---

## 2. 🎯 Objectives & Success Metrics

### Objectives
- Reduce call center queries  
- Improve customer satisfaction  
- Enable 24/7 access  

### KPIs
- 40% reduction in policy-related calls  
- < 5 sec response time  
- 80% successful query resolution  
- CSAT > 4.5  

---

## 3. 👤 User Personas

### Persona 1: Busy Professional
- Needs quick info  
- Prefers WhatsApp over calls  

### Persona 2: Senior Citizen
- Needs simple interaction  
- Avoids complex apps  

---

## 4. 📊 Use Cases

- Check policy status  
- View premium details  
- Download policy document  
- Check expiry date  

---

## 5. 🧩 Features

### Core Features
- Policy status check  
- Premium details  
- Policy download (PDF)  
- Expiry reminder  

### Supporting Features
- OTP-based authentication  
- Error handling messages  
- Retry mechanism  

---

## 6. 🧵 User Stories

- As a user, I want to check my policy status so that I know if it is active  
- As a user, I want to download my policy so that I can keep a copy  
- As a user, I want to see premium details so that I know payment info  

---

## 7. ✅ Acceptance Criteria

### Policy Status
- Given valid policy number  
- When user requests status  
- Then system should return correct policy status  

### Invalid Case
- Given invalid policy number  
- Then show error message  

---

## 8. 🔄 User Flow (High-Level)

1. User sends message: “Check policy”  
2. Bot asks for policy number  
3. User enters policy number  
4. System validates  
5. Fetch data from backend  
6. Return response  

